# Modern data platform architecture unifies storage, processing, and governance
@type: two_column

@col:
  ## Medallion Architecture (Recommended)
  - Bronze layer: raw ingestion from all source systems
  - Silver layer: cleaned, validated, conformed data
  - Gold layer: business-ready datasets and aggregations
  - Separation of storage (object store) from compute
  - Enables: streaming and batch on same data infrastructure

@col:
  ## Governance and Access
  - Unified data catalog with business-friendly metadata
  - Column-level access controls with role-based permissions
  - Data lineage tracking from source to dashboard
  - Automated data quality monitoring with alerting
  - Self-serve access for analysts without engineering tickets

@notes: The medallion architecture is the right choice for this organization's scale. It provides the clean separation needed for governance without sacrificing flexibility.

