# Platform build follows a 24-month sequence from foundation to self-serve
@type: timeline

@step: Months 1–6 | Foundation | Cloud infrastructure, bronze/silver ingestion, core 5 data domains
@step: Months 7–12 | Analytics Layer | Gold models, semantic layer, BI tool standardization
@step: Months 13–18 | Self-Serve | Data catalog, governed self-serve access, analyst workspace
@step: Months 19–24 | AI-Ready | Feature store, ML infrastructure, real-time streaming layer

@source: McKinsey Data Platform Implementation Methodology, 2024

@notes: Months 1–6 are the critical investment period. The platform will not produce visible business value until Month 8–10. Managing executive patience through this period requires clear milestone communication.

